  <mainDescription>Requirements traceability matrix helps to ensure each requirement adds value by relating it to the business and project
        objectives. It enables product requirements to be tracked throughout the project life cycle. This helps to ensure that
        solutions for each requirement is delivered at the end of the project. It also assists for managing changes to the product
        scope.&lt;br style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot; />
         The requirements traceability matrix also captures attributes associated with each requirement. They help to define
        specific information about the requirement. These attributes include, but not limited to, a unique identifier the
        description of the requirement, the owner, source, version, current status, priority, etc.&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <impactOfNotHaving>Not having a requirements traceabilty matrix may result in missed requirements in the finished product.&lt;br /></impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>Smaller project with only a few requirements may not require a requirements traceability matrix.&lt;br /></reasonsForNotNeeding>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
